            <h1 class="blueHead2"> Baggage Protection - A Comprehensive Overview</h1>
           
             <p>Please note that this service is provided on ${data.siteName} by Blue Ribbon Bags.</p>
            <ul class="content-list">
              <li>Once added to your booking, Blue Ribbon Bags (BRB) will track your delayed baggage and speed up its return within 96 hours <br />(4 days of your flight arrival) of it being lost. </li>
			   <li>Each purchase of BRB is per person, per round trip regardless of the number of connections on-route your flight. </li>
			   <li>The plan is categorized into three categories under which Blue Ribbon Bags will pay you:					  
			   <ul style="list-style:none; margin:10px 0; padding-left:20px;">
			    <!-- <li>$500 for $2.5 '<b>Silver</b>' Blue Ribbon Bags plan</li>-->
			   <li>$1,000 for $5 '<b>Gold</b>' Blue Ribbon Bags plan</li>
			   <li>$1,500 for $7.5 '<b>Platinum</b>' Blue Ribbon Bags plan</li>
			   <li>$2,000 for $10 '<b>Diamond</b>' Blue Ribbon Bags plan</li>
			   </ul>
			   
			   </li>
			   <li>It is important to note that BRB can be purchased any time prior to your flight - outbound or inbound and cannot be purchased while mid connection.</li>
			  <li>For your convenience, you will receive automatic updates for every change to your airline file. </li>
			  <li>We require no proof of the details of the contents in your bag. </li>
			  <li>Even if you receive your bags post the deadline of 96 hours, you would still be entitled of the  payment.</li>
			  <li>BRB service is completely non-refundable or non-transferable. In case your flight gets cancelled, there will be no credit or refund. You will have to purchase a new BRB plan with every new booking. </li>
            </ul>
            <h4>What to do in case you lose your baggage?</h4>
            <ul class="content-list">
            
            <li>One is REQUIRED to report their Mishandled Baggage to Blue Ribbon Bags within 24 hours of their flight landing.</li>
            <li>
					 In event of the lost luggage, you can file a mishandled baggage report with BRB by going to our website at <a
						href="https://www.blueribbonbags.com">www.blueribbonbags.com</a>, or by calling our MBR number at 888-BAGGAGE. we do not accept Mishandled Baggage Report submissions by email
					</li>
  <li>You will be required  to claim your lost baggage with your airline before reporting it to Blue Ribbon  Bags. </li>
  
			</ul>

